<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
<taxonomicName authority="Bourne, 1883" authorityName="Bourne" authorityYear="1883" class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Manayunkia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Manayunkia aestuarina" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aestuarina">Manayunkia aestuarina (Bourne, 1883)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. In the Mediterranean only reported from Greece (
<bibRefCitation author="Kisseleva, MI" journalOrPublisher="Studies of Sevastopol Biological Station" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="135 - 146" title="Qualitative and quantitative distribution of the benthos in the area surrounding Dardanelles, Aegean Sea" volume="14" year="1961">Kisseleva 1961</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Diapoulis, A" journalOrPublisher="Thalassographica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="127 - 139" title="Preliminary study of soft substrate macrozoobenthos and marine flora in the Bay of Gera (Lesvos Island, Greece)" volume="6" year="1983">Diapoulis and Bogdanos 1983</bibRefCitation>
). Both Greek records are from a fully marine environment and therefore considered questionable by 
<bibRefCitation author="Arvanitidis, Christos" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, Thessaloniki" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Συστηματική και βιονομική μελέτη των μακροβενθικών πολυxαίτων (AnnelidaPolychaeta) του Βορείου Αιγαίου" year="1994">Arvanitidis (1994)</bibRefCitation>
, as the species usually occurs in brackish waters. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Harris, Tegwyn" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Experimental Marine Biology and Ecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="105 - 112" title="The occurrence of Manayunkiaaestuarina (Bourne) and Mercierellaenigmatica Fauvel (Polychaeta) in non-brackish water in Britain" volume="5" year="1970">Harris (1970)</bibRefCitation>
reports the species from non-brackish environments in the British Isles and assumes that it can tolerate full salinity at least during certain stages of its life cycle. Based on the geographic range of 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Manayunkia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Manayunkia aestuarina" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aestuarina">Manayunkia aestuarina</taxonomicName>
, the Greek records must nevertheless be considered uncertain. Undescribed species of 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Fabriciidae" genus="Manayunkia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Manayunkia" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Manayunkia</taxonomicName>
exist in Greece (
<bibRefCitation author="Chintiroglou, Chariton-Charles" journalOrPublisher="Rapport et Proces-Verbaux des Reunions de la Commission Internationale pour l'Exploration Scientifique de la Mer Mediterranee" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination=": 506" title="Contribution to the knowledge of the macrobenthic biodiversity of Vouliagmeni Lagoon (Attica, Greece)" volume="37" year="2004">Chintiroglou et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
) and the genus needs further study in the region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
